Home, July 15, 1856
Dear Brother;
I was sorry to leave so unceremoniously without bidding you good bye, but so it seemed to happen and I could not have it otherwise. Hope you returned comfortably to our Graefenburg home last evening without feeling much fatigued from your days stay at Utica. You will observe that I left my work-box with needles and thread be. - for your convenience, also your folio. Your best vest and pants I put in a band box under the table.
